SHELL(1)

NAME
    shell - start the SmallOS command shell

SYNOPSIS
    shell [--line-mode]

DESCRIPTION
    shell starts the interactive SmallOS command shell. It is normally launched
    at boot after the kernel mounts ext2.

    The shell resolves external commands from /bin, /usr/bin, and /usr/sbin.
    Command names may omit the .elf suffix. A command containing a slash is
    treated as a path.

    The shell also implements a small set of built-ins for navigation,
    command execution, background jobs, and tests.

OPTIONS
    --line-mode
        Use simple line input instead of the interactive input path.

BUILT-INS
    help
        Show the command summary.

    cd path
        Change the shell working directory.

    pwd
    wd
        Print the shell working directory.

    runelf path [arg ...]
        Execute an ELF and wait for it to exit.

    runelf_nowait path [arg ...]
        Execute an ELF and return immediately.

    runelf_bg path [arg ...]
    bg path [arg ...]
        Execute an ELF as a reattachable background job.

    jobs
        List reattachable background jobs.

    fg jobid
        Reattach and wait for a background job.

    kill jobid
        Terminate a background job.

    selftest
        Run installed ELF self-tests.

    shelltest
        Run built-in shell parser and dispatch tests.

    clear
        Clear the terminal.

    exit
        Exit the shell.

PIPES
    A simple pipeline operator is supported:

        command1 | command2 | command3

SEE ALSO
    cd(1), runelf(1), jobs(1), fg(1), bg(1)
